{{- /*
kde-guard.sh.tmpl — KDE Plasma host guard, resolved from the fact registry.

`desktop` is a named host fact (.chezmoidata/facts.yaml → .chezmoitemplates/
facts.tmpl). The verdict is the one this guard always gave — desktop=kde IS
`plasmashell` on PATH, the shell binary the ISO shipped, stable from first boot —
but it is now probed ONCE per chezmoi command and BAKED IN by facts-sh.tmpl,
instead of re-derived by a `command -v` at each of the 15 include sites.

Deploy-everywhere-and-self-select is unchanged (KTD12): a non-KDE host exits 0,
so this stays a runtime skip, not a non-deployment gate. The skip message is the
pre-registry one, verbatim.

Baking the fact means a desktop swap changes this partial's rendered output, and
with it the content of every consuming run_onchange_ script — so they all re-run.
That is correct, not churn: the host became a different host.

ARGUMENT — a dict, NOT the bare display-name string this partial used to take:

  {{ includeTemplate "kde-guard.sh.tmpl" (dict "ctx" . "name" "my-script.sh") }}

facts-sh.tmpl needs the chezmoi context (.chezmoi.*, .factRegistry), and a
partial's `.` is only ever what its caller passed: there is no route back to the
root context from inside one — chezmoi exposes no `data` template function, and
`includeTemplate` takes exactly one data argument. So the caller hands over both,
the way fingerprint.tmpl already does. A call site still passing a bare string
aborts the apply with a message naming the fix, rather than rendering a guard
whose FACT_DESKTOP is unset and which would therefore never fire.

Consumers get the WHOLE FACT_* set in scope for free — do NOT inline
facts-sh.tmpl again alongside this guard.
*/ -}}
{{- if not (kindIs "map" .) -}}
{{-   fail (printf "kde-guard.sh.tmpl: expected a dict, got a %s (%v). This guard inlines facts-sh.tmpl, which needs the chezmoi context, so the call site must pass it: {{ includeTemplate \"kde-guard.sh.tmpl\" (dict \"ctx\" . \"name\" %q) }}" (kindOf .) . .) -}}
{{- end -}}
{{- $name := .name -}}
{{ includeTemplate "facts-sh.tmpl" .ctx }}
if [[ "$FACT_DESKTOP" != kde ]]; then
  printf '%s: plasmashell not found (non-KDE system), skipping.\n' '{{ $name }}'
  exit 0
fi
